cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SP, cs.NA, cs.CV 

The paper deals with dictionary learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and signal processing. The paper proposes an algorithm to learn computationally efficient dictionaries and their fast implementation, which involves optimization and linear algebra techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper mentions the factorization of the Hadamard matrix, which is a topic in numerical analysis and linear algebra, suggesting cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as another possible category. Finally, the paper demonstrates the approach with synthetic dictionary learning experiments, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
